{
    "summaryReport": "# Executive Summary: Technical Architecture and Reference Documentation\n\nTianwei Liu has shared a comprehensive set of resources in the `demo` channel, establishing the foundational architecture, templates, and external references for a new bot project. The shared documents focus heavily on Slack's Bolt framework, Prisma datastore integration, and Kubernetes community standards (specifically SIG-node and scheduling SIGs) to guide the team's development and governance processes.\n\n## Highlights\n* **Slack Bot Framework & Datastore**: Tianwei outlined the core stack, selecting [Slack Bolt JS](https://github.com/slackapi/bolt-js) for the bot framework and [Prisma](https://github.com/prisma/prisma) as the backing datastore.\n* **Standardized Proposal Templates**: The team is encouraged to use a consistent [Design-Doc Template](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1cE5zrjrR40RXNg64XtRFewSv6FrLV6slGkkqxBumS1w/edit) paired with the [Kubernetes KEP format](https://github.com/kubernetes/enhancements) for writing proposals.\n* **Kubernetes SIG Alignment**: Multiple references were shared to align with Kubernetes SIG-node and scheduling SIG processes, including the [SIG-Node README](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/sig-node/README.md) and [Scheduling SIG Notes](https://docs.google.com/document/d/13mwye7nvrmV11q9_Eg77z-1w3X7Q1GTbslpml4J7F3A/edit) to model batching and cadence.\n* **Active Contributor**: Tianwei Liu was the sole contributor in this batch, driving the documentation and architectural alignment.",
